column3: “Ilera I-95 smells like a diesel soaked skunk carcass along the side of I-95 during 5 o'clock traffic on a summer day and leaves your mouth tasting like you just finished following a Kenworth with leaky valves for 50 miles on your Harley. So you can expect an interesting high. It gave me a nice relaxing afternoon head buzz. The fuzzy and sticky buds ground to a nice volume and produced a dense vapor. Seemed to last lo...”
“Very strong awesome strain! LOVE this flavor profile!”
“My favorite strain out there great taste ,smell and high a must for true smokers”
“The smell of it is amazing. The high is great for a day in the beach.”
“Buena, me activa, exelente para trabajar durante el dia,”
“got blasted just after a couple bowls. tasted great, and gave me a good high.”

“This shit is so good I lost my Vape pen I got stoned out of my tits and lost it I had to go buy another one hopefully I won’t lose this one and my boy got so damn high he stuck in he stuck in the grip”
“I didn't care for this strain. It made me jumpy and anxious.”

“I was looking for something to cure my pain and maybe help me sleep, and while this kind of helped, I felt completely brain dead, something I really dislike when consuming cannabis. It’s rare a strain makes me feel like this, but trying this then others and then back to this I ended up giving the rest away which was a bummer considering it was top shelf @ 15$ a gram. Helps with the pain, and if you have ptsd/ anxiety...”
“They're actually IS an I-95 going from North Dakota to South Dakota.”
